###
### Embabel Ticket Triage Agent – REST examples
### Project: 02-embabel-ticket-triage
### Embabel: 0.4.0-SNAPSHOT | Spring Boot 3.5.13 | Java 21
### Mode: Spring Boot REST (programmatic invocation via AgentPlatform)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Export OPENAI_API_KEY
###   2. Start the app: mvn spring-boot:run
###
### Demo walkthrough order:
###   1. Flow A — Normal incident (deterministic, no LLM)
###   2. Flow B — Uncertain case (replanning inserts deepClassify with LLM)
###   3. Flow C — Security fast-path (deterministic CRITICAL)
###   4. Flow D — Classic service request (LLM-assisted priority)
###   5. Flow E — Outage + VIP deadline (deterministic CRITICAL)
###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@triageEndpoint = {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/triage

### ─── Flow A: Normal Incident ───────────────────────────────────────────────
### Deterministic incident path with no replanning.
### Expected:
### - extractSignals -> SignalsOk(security=false, outage=true, vip=false)
### - quickClassifyOk -> ConfidentCategory(INCIDENT, confidence=0.85)
### - NO deepClassify
### - assessPriority: outage => HIGH (deterministic)
### - route: targetTeam=platform-ops
###
### Trace must NOT contain:
###   - "deepClassify:"
###

POST {{triageEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketId": "INC-101",
  "text": "VPN has not been working since this morning. Multiple employees are reporting an outage.",
  "channel": "email",
  "simulate": "NORMAL"
}

###

### ─── Flow B: Uncertain Case / Replanning ──────────────────────────────────
### Low-confidence path that forces an LLM-backed replan.
### Expected:
### - extractSignals -> SignalsNeedsDeep(reason=simulate=LOW_CONFIDENCE)
### - quickClassifyNeedsDeep -> UncertainCategory(bestGuess=SERVICE_REQUEST, confidence=0.45, ...)
### - Replanning inserts deepClassify (LLM) to produce ConfidentCategory
### - assessPriority uses LLM (non-outage path)
### - route result depends on category (in sample response: platform-ops)
###
### Trace MUST contain (proof of replanning):
###   - "quickClassify: UncertainCategory"
###   - "deepClassify: invoking LLM to resolve uncertainty"
###

POST {{triageEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketId": "REQ-202",
  "text": "I cannot log in, but sometimes it works. Please investigate.",
  "channel": "web",
  "simulate": "LOW_CONFIDENCE"
}

###

### ─── Flow C: Security Fast-Path ────────────────────────────────────────────
### Deterministic escalation for a security incident.
### Expected:
### - extractSignals -> SignalsOk(security=true, outage=false, vip=false)
### - Category: SECURITY
### - assessPriority: SECURITY => CRITICAL (deterministic)
### - Routing: security-incident
###
### Trace MUST contain:
###   - "assessPriority: SECURITY => CRITICAL (deterministic)"
###

POST {{triageEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketId": "SEC-777",
  "text": "Possible data leak: an employee opened a phishing link and credentials may be compromised.",
  "channel": "phone",
  "simulate": "NORMAL"
}

###

### ─── Flow D: Classic Service Request ───────────────────────────────────────
### Typical request path with LLM-assisted priority assessment.
### Expected:
### - extractSignals -> SignalsOk(security=false, outage=false, vip=false)
### - Category: SERVICE_REQUEST
### - assessPriority: invoking LLM for non-outage
### - Priority: LOW|MEDIUM|HIGH|CRITICAL (in sample response: LOW)
### - Routing: service-desk-l1 (unless priority is HIGH/CRITICAL)
###
### Trace MUST contain:
###   - "assessPriority: invoking LLM for non-outage"
###

POST {{triageEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketId": "SR-314",
  "text": "Please grant a new permission for repository X. I need read-only access.",
  "channel": "email",
  "simulate": "NORMAL"
}

###

### ─── Flow E: Outage + VIP Deadline ────────────────────────────────────────
### Deterministic CRITICAL escalation without LLM involvement.
### Expected:
### - extractSignals -> SignalsOk(security=false, outage=true, vip=true)
### - Category: INCIDENT
### - assessPriority: outage+vip => CRITICAL (deterministic)
### - Routing: platform-ops
###
### Trace MUST contain:
###   - "assessPriority: outage+vip => CRITICAL (deterministic)"
###

POST {{triageEndpoint}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticketId": "INC-999",
  "text": "System is not reachable. A VIP customer meeting is scheduled in 30 minutes and executives are waiting.",
  "channel": "chat",
  "simulate": "NORMAL"
}

###
